                     <interp inst="t18260914-432-person2241" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-432-person2241" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Manchester-street. On the 15th of August, about four o'clock, I was in Mr. Limbert's shop, in <placeName id="t18260914-432-crimeloc2434">Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-432-crimeloc2434" type="placeName" value="Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-432-crimeloc2434" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-432-off2432 t18260914-432-crimeloc2434"></join>; the prisoner came in and asked to see some French cambric, which was shewn her - the shopman was called away and, in the meantime, I saw her take two parcels of cambric and put them up her clothes; she was going out - I said "Have you been served?" she said Yes - in half a minute a piece fell from her clothes on the floor; she wished to go, but I took her into the parlour, and told her to give up the other piece, and she dropped it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-432-person2242">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BALLARD
